data.chText: 搬出，腾出，空出（建筑物、座位等）
data.enText: to leave a building, seat, etc., especially so that sb else can use it

data.chText: 房客务请在离开之日的中午以前腾出房间。
data.enText: Guests are requested to vacate their rooms by noon on the day of departure.
to leave a job, position of authority, etc. so that it is available for sb else

simple_means.memory_skill: vac 空 + ate 使… → 弄空 → 腾空

means: 搬出，腾出，空出(建筑物、座位等)

example: He revoked the ban on smoking
You must vacate your office by tonight

tr: leave (a job, post, or position) voluntarily
example: She vacated the position when she got pregnant
The chairman resigned when he was found to have misappropriated funds

value.def: If you vacate a place or a job, you leave it or give it up, making it available for other people.

example.ex: He vacated the flat and went to stay with an uncle...
example.tran: 他搬出了公寓，住到了他的一个叔叔那里。

example.ex: He recently vacated his post as NHS Personnel Director...
example.tran: 他最近辞去了国民保健署人事主管一职。

example.ex: Chris slumped down in the chair Mrs Tennant had just vacated.
example.tran: 克里斯一屁股坐在坦南特夫人刚刚腾出的椅子上。

partsOfSpeech.dec: a 加强 + void 空 → 空出来 → 回避
de 加强 + void 空 → 空的 → 缺乏的
e 出 + vacu 空 + ate 使… → 空出去 → 撤离
e 出 + van 空 + escent 开始出现…的 → 开始变空的 → 消失的
un 不 + avoid 回避 + able 可…的 → 不可避免的
vac 空 + ant …的 → 空的；空闲的
vac 空 + ate 做，造成，使… → 弄空 → 腾空
vac 空 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 空出来不用干活 → 假期
vacu 空 + ous …的 → 空虚的；无意义的
vacu 空 + um → 空虚；真空
van 空 + ish 使… → 空空如也 → 消失
van 空 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 心里空空 → 空虚
